	            <h4>1. Smoking</h4>
	            <p>Smoking is by far the most important preventable cause of cancer. It is responsible for one in four UK cancer deaths, and nearly a fifth of all cancer cases. Nearly half of all smokers will eventually die from smoking-related diseases.<sup>2</sup>
	                <span class="nice_link"><a href="http://www.nice.org.uk/advice/lgb1"  class="external_link" target="_blank">More about smoking-related mortality</a></span>
